Senior administration officials, including Chief of Staff Rahm Emanuel and Assistant to the President for Energy and Climate Change Carol Browner, met with BP executives Bob Dudley and Lamar McKay to discuss ongoing clean-up and recovery efforts in the Gulf. They emphasized the importance of BP fulfilling their commitment to long-term recovery and assured that the administration will ensure this promise is met. Additionally, the officials stressed the need for BP to promptly pay state and local government claims and reiterated President Obama's dedication to holding BP accountable and addressing economic, health, and environmental needs in the region.